OL,3,CHosepipe ban announced for parts of
OL,4,Cwest Wales
OL,6,FDwr Cymru Welsh Water has announced a
OL,7,Fhosepipe ban affecting around 33,000
OL,8,Fproperties, which will come into force
OL,9,Fon Sunday 19 July.
OL,11,FThe ban will cover mid and south
OL,12,FCeredigion, parts of north
OL,13,FPembrokeshire and north
OL,14,FCarmarthenshire.
OL,16,FThose whose postcode falls under the
OL,17,Fban must not use a hosepipe to water
OL,18,Fgardens and plants, clean cars, fill
OL,19,Fswimming pools, fountains or ponds,
OL,20,Fclean domestic premises, and paths or
OL,21,Fpatios.
OL,26,@nD@Bs{
